Articles.Content: When I search for "KSP" in my web browser, using google, the second result that comes up is the Kentucky State Police. What comes up in your search engine, or is it the same for everyone?

It depends on your location and - if you are logged in - on a number of other factors.

I get tons of german organizations from scientific publishing through tax advice and care for the elderly plus the inadvertable KSP disambiguation page for the german wikipedia. (The KSP article there was apparently written by a fourteen year old.)

Edited July 30, 2013 by jfx
Russian google, not logged in:
After The main page, the forum, The Reddit Page, Space Port, two video's and the wikipedia page, I get KSP world Tour which apparently is a "rider driven kite surf world championship tour".

After The main page, the forum, The Reddit Page, Space Port, two video's and the wikipedia page, I get KSP world Tour which apparently is a "rider driven kite surf world championship tour".

Same as me, but don't forget ksp.co.il, which appears to be an Israeli technology site (My Hebrew's not so good).

yea ksp.co.il is an Israeli computer/electronics store, I live in Israel so the first time i searched for ksp I had to write the whole thing because I only got results from ksp.co.il and their products.
There is also a Swedish machine gun called ksp m/42
Katharine Susannah Prichard Writers' Centre is the 1st non-Kerbal response in my google, it rates as 5th.

I get the KSP website, the wiki, the Kentucky State Police, some KSP youtube videos, the space port, two websites about solubility products, a vimeo video, the reddit, and then a door lock manufacture.

"KSP is a leading door lock manufacturer specializing in interchangeable cores and housings with mortise and rim designs."

I get the KSP website.

What's really depressing is if you type in ''KSP f'' instead of KSP forums it comes up ''KSP for free"
